Nasa keeps naming things we discover in foreign languages.

For example the Mars rover discoveries keep getting named in spanish. We are taxpayers in an english speaking nation.

NO MORE DISCOVERIES NAMED IN FOREIGN TONGUES!

It seems nasa will name everything in a language other than english:

* Aadir Crater (Arabic for "rare")
* Valiamala Crater (Malayalam for "big garland")
* Thumba Crater (Malayalam for "rocket launch site")
* Bekal Crater (Malayalam for "fort")
* Varkala Crater (Malayalam for "coastal town")
* Periyar Vallis (Malayalam for "great river")
* Krishnan Crater (Tamil-origin name for geologist)
* Krishnan Palus (Tamil-origin for "marsh")
* Ogygis Planum (Latin for "ancient")
* Babati Mons (Swahili for "town in Tanzania")
* Tokmok Crater (Kyrgyz for "hammer")
* Ubajara Rock (Portuguese for "Brazilian national park")
* Jezero Crater (Slavic for "lake")
* Neretva Vallis (Croatian for "river")
* Peace Vallis (Arabic for "peace")
* Cheyava Falls (Havasupai for "waterfall")
* Bright Angel (Native American for "formation")

Stop it, we're Americans!
